Upper lip (
Fig. 14D
) convex anteriorly, entire, covered with minute setae.

Maxilla 1 (
Fig. 14G, H
) outer lobe with nine dentate robust setae on apical margin; palp biarticulated, distal article curved, a little swollen, with five setae on apical margin.

Maxilla 2 (
Fig. 14I
) inner lobe with an oblique row of plumose setae on surface; outer lobe longer and slightly dilated distally than inner lobe.

Pereopod 4 (
Fig. 16A
) coxa not widened distally, slightly curved, half as wide as long, without stridulated ridges; other articles similar to those of pereopod 3 in shape, but plumose setae different in position.

Epimera 2 and 3 (
Fig. 16E
) each posterioventral corner produced backwards.

Telson (
Fig. 16I
) triangular in dorsal view, with a pair of simple setae and a pair of sensory setae on each side.

Oostegites on gnathopod 2 as long as that of pereopod 3. That of pereopod 5 0.7 x as long as that of pereopod 4 (
Fig. 17D, F-H
).
